66bool HasAttr(const NodeDef& node, const string& attr_name) {
67 return node.attr().count(attr_name) > 0;
68}
69
70const string& GetStringAttr(const NodeDef& node, const string& attr_name) {
71 CHECK(HasAttr(node, attr_name));
72 const auto& attr = node.attr().at(attr_name);
73 CHECK_EQ(attr.value_case(), AttrValue::kS);
74 return attr.s();
75}
76
77int64 GetIntAttr(const NodeDef& node, const string& attr_name) {
78 CHECK(HasAttr(node, attr_name)) << attr_name << " not found in:\n"
79 << node.DebugString();
80 const auto& attr = node.attr().at(attr_name);
81 CHECK_EQ(attr.value_case(), AttrValue::kI);
82 return attr.i();
83}
84
85float GetFloatAttr(const NodeDef& node, const string& attr_name) {
86 CHECK(HasAttr(node, attr_name));
87 const auto& attr = node.attr().at(attr_name);
88 CHECK_EQ(attr.value_case(), AttrValue::kF);
89 return attr.f();
90}
91
92bool GetBoolAttr(const NodeDef& node, const string& attr_name) {
93 CHECK(HasAttr(node, attr_name));
94 const auto& attr = node.attr().at(attr_name);
95 CHECK_EQ(attr.value_case(), AttrValue::kB);
96 return attr.b();
97}
98
99tensorflow::DataType GetDataTypeAttr(const NodeDef& node,
100 const string& attr_name) {
101 CHECK(HasAttr(node, attr_name));
102 const auto& attr = node.attr().at(attr_name);
103 CHECK_EQ(attr.value_case(), AttrValue::kType);
104 return attr.type();
105}
106
107const TensorShapeProto& GetShapeAttr(const NodeDef& node,
108 const string& attr_name) {
109 CHECK(HasAttr(node, attr_name));
110 const auto& attr = node.attr().at(attr_name);
111 CHECK_EQ(attr.value_case(), AttrValue::kShape);
112 return attr.shape();
113}
114
115const TensorProto& GetTensorAttr(const NodeDef& node, const string& attr_name) {
116 CHECK(HasAttr(node, attr_name));
117 const auto& attr = node.attr().at(attr_name);
118 CHECK_EQ(attr.value_case(), AttrValue::kTensor);
119 return attr.tensor();
120}
121
122const AttrValue::ListValue& GetListAttr(const NodeDef& node,
123 const string& attr_name) {
124 CHECK(HasAttr(node, attr_name));
125 const auto& attr = node.attr().at(attr_name);
126 CHECK_EQ(attr.value_case(), AttrValue::kList);
127 return attr.list();
128}
129
130ArrayDataType ConvertDataType(tensorflow::DataType dtype) {
131 if (dtype == DT_UINT8)
132 return ArrayDataType::kUint8;
133 else if (dtype == DT_FLOAT)
134 return ArrayDataType::kFloat;
135 else if (dtype == DT_BOOL)
136 return ArrayDataType::kBool;
137 else if (dtype == DT_INT32)
138 return ArrayDataType::kInt32;
139 else if (dtype == DT_INT64)
140 return ArrayDataType::kInt64;
141 else if (dtype == DT_STRING)
142 return ArrayDataType::kString;
143 else
144 LOG(INFO) << "Unsupported data type in placehoder op: " << dtype;
145 return ArrayDataType::kNone;
146}
147
148void ImportShape(const TFLITE_PROTO_NS::RepeatedPtrField<
149 tensorflow::TensorShapeProto_Dim>& input_dims,
150 Shape* shape) {
151 std::vector<int> input_dims_only_sizes;
152 for (auto& d : input_dims) {
153 if (d.size() == 0) {
154 // Some TensorFlow shapes contain a 0 dim, effectively making
155 // them of flat size 0 even though they have other nonzero dims.
156 // This breaks our invariant, that array dims can't be 0.
157 // For now, tweaking this to record a 0-D shape instead.
158 input_dims_only_sizes.clear();
159 break;
160 }
161 input_dims_only_sizes.push_back(d.size());
162 }
163 *shape->mutable_dims() = input_dims_only_sizes;
164}
165
166void ImportFloatArray(const TensorProto& input_tensor, Array* output_array) {
167 CHECK_EQ(input_tensor.dtype(), DT_FLOAT);
168 const auto& input_shape = input_tensor.tensor_shape();
169 CHECK_LE(input_shape.dim_size(), 4);
170 ImportShape(input_shape.dim(), output_array->mutable_shape());
171 int input_flat_size = 1;
172 for (int k = 0; k < input_shape.dim_size(); k++) {
173 input_flat_size *= input_shape.dim(k).size();
174 }
175 auto& output_float_data =
176 output_array->GetMutableBuffer<ArrayDataType::kFloat>().data;
177 output_float_data.resize(RequiredBufferSizeForShape(output_array->shape()),
178 0.f);
179 if (input_tensor.float_val_size() == 1) {
180 for (int i = 0; i < input_flat_size; i++) {
181 output_float_data[i] = input_tensor.float_val(0);
182 }
183 } else if (input_tensor.float_val_size() == input_flat_size) {
184 for (int i = 0; i < input_tensor.float_val_size(); i++) {
185 output_float_data[i] = input_tensor.float_val(i);
186 }
187 } else if (input_tensor.tensor_content().size() ==
188 input_flat_size * sizeof(float)) {
189 toco::port::CopyToBuffer(input_tensor.tensor_content(),
190 reinterpret_cast<char*>(output_float_data.data()));
191 } else {
192 LOG(FATAL) << "Neither input_content nor float_val have the right "
193 "dimensions for this float tensor.";
194 }
195}
196
197void ImportQuint8Array(const TensorProto& input_tensor, Array* output_array) {
198 CHECK_EQ(input_tensor.dtype(), DT_QUINT8);
199 const auto& input_shape = input_tensor.tensor_shape();
200 CHECK_LE(input_shape.dim_size(), 4);
201 ImportShape(input_shape.dim(), output_array->mutable_shape());
202 int input_flat_size = 1;
203 for (int k = 0; k < input_shape.dim_size(); k++) {
204 input_flat_size *= input_shape.dim(k).size();
205 }
206 auto& output_int_data =
207 output_array->GetMutableBuffer<ArrayDataType::kUint8>().data;
208 output_int_data.resize(RequiredBufferSizeForShape(output_array->shape()), 0);
209 if (input_tensor.int_val_size()) {
210 for (int i = 0; i < input_tensor.int_val_size(); i++) {
211 output_int_data[i] = input_tensor.int_val(i);
212 }
213 } else if (input_tensor.tensor_content().size() ==
214 input_flat_size * sizeof(uint8_t)) {
215 toco::port::CopyToBuffer(input_tensor.tensor_content(),
216 reinterpret_cast<char*>(output_int_data.data()));
217 } else {
218 LOG(FATAL) << "Neither input_content nor int_val have the right "
219 "dimensions for this uint8 tensor.";
220 }
221}

275void ImportBoolArray(const TensorProto& input_tensor, Array* output_array) {
276 CHECK_EQ(input_tensor.dtype(), DT_BOOL);
277 const auto& input_shape = input_tensor.tensor_shape();
278 CHECK_LE(input_shape.dim_size(), 4);
279 ImportShape(input_shape.dim(), output_array->mutable_shape());
280 int input_flat_size = 1;
281 for (int k = 0; k < input_shape.dim_size(); k++) {
282 input_flat_size *= input_shape.dim(k).size();
283 }
284 auto& output_bool_data =
285 output_array->GetMutableBuffer<ArrayDataType::kBool>().data;
286 output_bool_data.resize(RequiredBufferSizeForShape(output_array->shape()),
287 false);
288 if (input_tensor.bool_val_size()) {
289 for (int i = 0; i < input_tensor.bool_val_size(); i++) {
290 output_bool_data[i] = input_tensor.bool_val(i);
291 }
292 } else if (input_tensor.tensor_content().size() == input_flat_size) {
293 std::vector<char> buf(input_tensor.tensor_content().size());
294 toco::port::CopyToBuffer(input_tensor.tensor_content(), buf.data());
295 for (int i = 0; i < input_tensor.tensor_content().size(); i++) {
296 output_bool_data[i] = static_cast<bool>(buf[i]);
297 }
298 } else {
299 // Some graphs have bool const nodes without actual value...
300 // assuming that 'false' is implied.
301 // So far only encountered that in an array with 1 entry, let's
302 // require that until we encounter a graph where that's not the case.
303 CHECK_EQ(output_bool_data.size(), 1);
304 output_bool_data[0] = false;
305 }
306}
307
308void ImportStringArray(const TensorProto& input_tensor, Array* output_array) {
309 CHECK_EQ(input_tensor.dtype(), DT_STRING);
310 const auto& input_shape = input_tensor.tensor_shape();
311 CHECK_LE(input_shape.dim_size(), 4);
312 ImportShape(input_shape.dim(), output_array->mutable_shape());
313 int input_flat_size = 1;
314 for (int k = 0; k < input_shape.dim_size(); k++) {
315 input_flat_size *= input_shape.dim(k).size();
316 }
317 auto& output_string_data =
318 output_array->GetMutableBuffer<ArrayDataType::kString>().data;
319 output_string_data.resize(RequiredBufferSizeForShape(output_array->shape()));
320 if (input_flat_size != input_tensor.string_val_size()) {
321 LOG(FATAL) << "Input_content string_val doesn't have the right "
322 "dimensions for this string tensor.";
323 }
324 for (int i = 0; i < input_flat_size; ++i) {
325 output_string_data[i] = input_tensor.string_val(i);
326 }
327}
328
329// Count the number of inputs of a given node. If
330// `tf_import_flags.drop_control_dependency` is true, count the number of
331// non-control-dependency inputs.
332int GetInputsCount(const NodeDef& node,
333 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags) {
334 if (tf_import_flags.drop_control_dependency) {
335 for (size_t i = 0; i < node.input_size(); ++i) {
336 if (node.input(i)[0] == '^') {
337 return i;
338 }
339 }
340 return node.input_size();
341 } else {
342 return node.input_size();
343 }
344}
345
346void CheckInputsCount(const NodeDef& node,
347 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
348 int expected_input_count) {
349 QCHECK_EQ(GetInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags), expected_input_count)
350 << node.op() << " node expects " << expected_input_count
351 << " input(s) other than control dependencies: " << node.DebugString();
352}
353
354template <ArrayDataType T>
355string CreateConstArray(Model* model, string const& name,
356 std::vector<typename toco::DataType<T> > const& data) {
357 // Utility function to create a const 1D array, useful for input parameters.
358 string array_name = toco::AvailableArrayName(*model, name);
359 auto& array = model->GetOrCreateArray(array_name);
360 array.data_type = T;
361 array.mutable_shape()->mutable_dims()->emplace_back(data.size());
362 array.GetMutableBuffer<T>().data = data;
363 return array_name;
364}
365
366void ConvertConstOperator(const NodeDef& node,
367 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
368 Model* model) {
369 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "Const");
370 const auto& tensor = GetTensorAttr(node, "value");
371 const auto dtype = GetDataTypeAttr(node, "dtype");
372
373 auto& array = model->GetOrCreateArray(node.name());
374 switch (dtype) {
375 case DT_FLOAT:
376 array.data_type = ArrayDataType::kFloat;
377 ImportFloatArray(tensor, &array);
378 break;
379 case DT_INT32:
380 array.data_type = ArrayDataType::kInt32;
381 ImportInt32Array(tensor, &array);
382 break;
383 case DT_QUINT8:
384 array.data_type = ArrayDataType::kUint8;
385 ImportQuint8Array(tensor, &array);
386 break;
387 case DT_INT64:
388 array.data_type = ArrayDataType::kInt64;
389 ImportInt64Array(tensor, &array);
390 break;
391 case DT_STRING:
392 array.data_type = ArrayDataType::kString;
393 ImportStringArray(tensor, &array);
394 break;
395 case DT_BOOL:
396 array.data_type = ArrayDataType::kBool;
397 ImportBoolArray(tensor, &array);
398 break;
399 default:
400 array.data_type = ArrayDataType::kNone;
401 // do nothing, silently ignore the Const data.
402 // We just make a dummy buffer to indicate that
403 // this array does not rely on external input.
404 array.GetMutableBuffer<ArrayDataType::kNone>();
405 break;
406 }
407}
408
409void ConvertConvOperator(const NodeDef& node,
410 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
411 Model* model) {
412 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "Conv2D");
413 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 2);
414
415 // We only support NHWC, which is the default data_format.
416 // So if data_format is not defined, we're all good.
417 if (HasAttr(node, "data_format")) {
418 CHECK_EQ(GetStringAttr(node, "data_format"), "NHWC");
419 }
420 CHECK_EQ(GetDataTypeAttr(node, "T"), DT_FLOAT);
421
422 const auto& input_name = node.input(0);
423 const auto& weights_name = node.input(1);
424 const auto& reordered_weights_name = weights_name + "_reordered";
425 // Check if a ReorderAxesOperator was already created for these weights
426 // (that happens when multiple layers share the same weights).
427 const Operator* existing_reorder =
428 GetOpWithOutput(*model, reordered_weights_name);
429 if (existing_reorder) {
430 // Check that it is safe to rely on the _reordered naming of the output
431 // array!
432 CHECK(existing_reorder->type == OperatorType::kReorderAxes);
433 } else {
434 // Create a new ReorderAxesOperator
435 auto* reorder = new ReorderAxesOperator;
436 reorder->inputs = {weights_name};
437 reorder->outputs = {reordered_weights_name};
438 reorder->input_axes_order = AxesOrder::kHWIO;
439 reorder->output_axes_order = AxesOrder::kOHWI;
440 model->operators.emplace_back(reorder);
441 }
442 auto* conv = new ConvOperator;
443 conv->inputs = {input_name, reordered_weights_name};
444 conv->outputs = {node.name()};
445 const auto& strides = GetListAttr(node, "strides");
446 CHECK_EQ(strides.i_size(), 4);
447 CHECK_EQ(strides.i(0), 1);
448 CHECK_EQ(strides.i(3), 1);
449 conv->stride_height = strides.i(1);
450 conv->stride_width = strides.i(2);
451 if (HasAttr(node, "dilations")) {
452 const auto& dilations = GetListAttr(node, "dilations");
453 CHECK_EQ(dilations.i_size(), 4);
454 CHECK_EQ(dilations.i(0), 1);
455 CHECK_EQ(dilations.i(3), 1);
456 conv->dilation_height_factor = dilations.i(1);
457 conv->dilation_width_factor = dilations.i(2);
458 } else {
459 conv->dilation_height_factor = 1;
460 conv->dilation_width_factor = 1;
461 }
462 const auto& padding = GetStringAttr(node, "padding");
463 if (padding == "SAME") {
464 conv->padding.type = PaddingType::kSame;
465 } else if (padding == "VALID") {
466 conv->padding.type = PaddingType::kValid;
467 } else {
468 LOG(FATAL) << "Bad padding (only SAME and VALID are supported)";
469 }
470 model->operators.emplace_back(conv);
471}

473void ConvertDepthwiseConvOperator(const NodeDef& node,
474 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
475 Model* model) {
476 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "DepthwiseConv2dNative");
477 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 2);
478
479 // We only support NHWC, which is the default data_format.
480 // So if data_format is not defined, we're all good.
481 if (HasAttr(node, "data_format")) {
482 CHECK_EQ(GetStringAttr(node, "data_format"), "NHWC");
483 }
484 CHECK_EQ(GetDataTypeAttr(node, "T"), DT_FLOAT);
485
486 const auto& input_name = node.input(0);
487 const auto& weights_name = node.input(1);
488 const auto& reordered_weights_name = weights_name + "_reordered";
489 // Check if a ReorderAxesOperator was already created for these weights
490 // (that happens when multiple layers share the same weights).
491 const Operator* existing_reorder =
492 GetOpWithOutput(*model, reordered_weights_name);
493 if (existing_reorder) {
494 // Check that it is safe to rely on the _reordered naming of the output
495 // array!
496 CHECK(existing_reorder->type == OperatorType::kReorderAxes);
497 } else {
498 // Create a new ReorderAxesOperator
499 auto* reorder = new ReorderAxesOperator;
500 reorder->inputs = {weights_name};
501 reorder->outputs = {reordered_weights_name};
502 reorder->input_axes_order = AxesOrder::kHWIM;
503 reorder->output_axes_order = AxesOrder::k1HWO;
504 model->operators.emplace_back(reorder);
505 }
506 auto* conv = new DepthwiseConvOperator;
507 conv->inputs = {input_name, reordered_weights_name};
508 conv->outputs = {node.name()};
509 const auto& strides = GetListAttr(node, "strides");
510 CHECK_EQ(strides.i_size(), 4);
511 CHECK_EQ(strides.i(0), 1);
512 CHECK_EQ(strides.i(3), 1);
513 conv->stride_height = strides.i(1);
514 conv->stride_width = strides.i(2);
515 const auto& padding = GetStringAttr(node, "padding");
516 if (padding == "SAME") {
517 conv->padding.type = PaddingType::kSame;
518 } else if (padding == "VALID") {
519 conv->padding.type = PaddingType::kValid;
520 } else {
521 LOG(FATAL) << "Bad padding (only SAME and VALID are supported)";
522 }
523 model->operators.emplace_back(conv);
524}

526void ConvertDepthToSpaceOperator(const NodeDef& node,
527 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
528 Model* model) {
529 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "DepthToSpace");
530 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 1);
531
532 CHECK_EQ(GetDataTypeAttr(node, "T"), DT_FLOAT);
533 auto* op = new DepthToSpaceOperator;
534 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
535 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
536 op->block_size = GetIntAttr(node, "block_size");
537 QCHECK_GE(op->block_size, 2);
538 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
539}

556void ConvertBiasAddOperator(const NodeDef& node,
557 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
558 Model* model) {
559 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "BiasAdd");
560 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 2);
561
562 const auto& input_name = node.input(0);
563 const auto& bias_name = node.input(1);
564 CHECK_EQ(GetDataTypeAttr(node, "T"), DT_FLOAT);
565 auto* biasadd = new AddOperator;
566 biasadd->inputs.push_back(input_name);
567 biasadd->inputs.push_back(bias_name);
568 biasadd->outputs.push_back(node.name());
569 model->operators.emplace_back(biasadd);
570}
571
572void ConvertRandomUniform(const NodeDef& node,
573 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
574 Model* model) {
575 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "RandomUniform");
576 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 1);
577
578 CHECK_EQ(GetDataTypeAttr(node, "T"), DT_INT32);
579 auto op = absl::make_unique<RandomUniformOperator>();
580 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
581 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
582 op->dtype = ConvertDataType(GetDataTypeAttr(node, "dtype"));
583 op->seed = GetIntAttr(node, "seed");
584 op->seed2 = GetIntAttr(node, "seed2");
585 CHECK(model != nullptr);
586 model->operators.emplace_back(std::move(op));
587}

664void ConvertIdentityOperator(const NodeDef& node,
665 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
666 Model* model) {
667 CHECK(node.op() == "Identity" || node.op() == "CheckNumerics" ||
668 node.op() == "PlaceholderWithDefault" || node.op() == "StopGradient");
669 auto* op = new TensorFlowIdentityOperator;
670 // Amazingly, some TensorFlow graphs (at least rajeev_lstm.pb) have
671 // identity nodes with multiple inputs, but the other inputs seem
672 // to be gratuitous (in the case of rajeev_lstm.pb, these are
673 // enumerating the LSTM state arrays). We will just ignore extra
674 // inputs beyond the first input.
675 QCHECK_GE(node.input_size(), 1)
676 << node.op()
677 << " node expects at least 1 input other than control dependencies: "
678 << node.DebugString();
679 const auto& input_name = node.input(0);
680 op->inputs.push_back(input_name);
681 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
682 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
683}

685void ConvertFakeQuantWithMinMaxArgs(

687 Model* model) {

692 op->minmax.reset(new MinMax);
693 auto& minmax = *op->minmax;
694 minmax.min = GetFloatAttr(node, "min");

978
979void ConvertMaxPoolOperator(const NodeDef& node,
980 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
981 Model* model) {
982 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "MaxPool");
983 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 1);
984 const auto& input_name = node.input(0);
985 // We only support NHWC, which is the default data_format.
986 // So if data_format is not defined, we're all good.
987 if (node.attr().count("data_format")) {
988 CHECK_EQ(GetStringAttr(node, "data_format"), "NHWC");
989 }
990 if (HasAttr(node, "T")) {
991 CHECK_EQ(GetDataTypeAttr(node, "T"), DT_FLOAT);
992 } else {
993 LOG(WARNING) << "Found MaxPool operator missing 'T' attribute";
994 }
995 auto* maxpool = new MaxPoolOperator;
996 maxpool->inputs.push_back(input_name);
997 maxpool->outputs.push_back(node.name());
998 const auto& strides = GetListAttr(node, "strides");
999 CHECK_EQ(strides.i_size(), 4);
1000 CHECK_EQ(strides.i(0), 1);
1001 CHECK_EQ(strides.i(3), 1);
1002 maxpool->stride_height = strides.i(1);
1003 maxpool->stride_width = strides.i(2);
1004 const auto& ksize = GetListAttr(node, "ksize");
1005 CHECK_EQ(ksize.i_size(), 4);
1006 CHECK_EQ(ksize.i(0), 1);
1007 CHECK_EQ(ksize.i(3), 1);
1008 maxpool->kheight = ksize.i(1);
1009 maxpool->kwidth = ksize.i(2);
1010 const auto& padding = GetStringAttr(node, "padding");
1011 if (padding == "SAME") {
1012 maxpool->padding.type = PaddingType::kSame;
1013 } else if (padding == "VALID") {
1014 maxpool->padding.type = PaddingType::kValid;
1015 } else {
1016 LOG(FATAL) << "Bad padding (only SAME and VALID are supported)";
1017 }
1018 model->operators.emplace_back(maxpool);
1019}

1021void ConvertAvgPoolOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1022 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1023 Model* model) {
1024 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "AvgPool");
1025 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 1);

1031 }

1033 auto* avgpool = new AveragePoolOperator;
1034 avgpool->inputs.push_back(input_name);

1036 const auto& strides = GetListAttr(node, "strides");
1037 CHECK_EQ(strides.i_size(), 4);

1039 CHECK_EQ(strides.i(3), 1);

1071void ConvertBatchMatMulOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1072 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1073 Model* model) {
1074 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 2);
1075
1076 // https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.12/api_docs/python/math_ops/matrix_math_functions
1077 CHECK(!HasAttr(node, "adj_a") || (GetBoolAttr(node, "adj_a") == false));
1078 CHECK(!HasAttr(node, "adj_b") || (GetBoolAttr(node, "adj_b") == false));
1079
1080 auto* batch_matmul = new BatchMatMulOperator;
1081 batch_matmul->inputs = {node.input(0), node.input(1)};
1082 batch_matmul->outputs = {node.name()};
1083 model->operators.emplace_back(batch_matmul);
1084}

1086void ConvertMatMulOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1087 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1088 Model* model) {
1089 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 2);
1090
1091 // Transpose flags should be easy to support, but we don't have a
1092 // GraphDef with them to test on at the moment.
1093 CHECK_EQ(GetBoolAttr(node, "transpose_a"), false);
1094 CHECK_EQ(GetBoolAttr(node, "transpose_b"), false);
1095 CHECK(!HasAttr(node, "adjoint_a") ||
1096 (GetBoolAttr(node, "adjoint_a") == false));
1097 CHECK(!HasAttr(node, "adjoint_b") ||
1098 (GetBoolAttr(node, "adjoint_b") == false));
1099
1100 auto* matmul = new TensorFlowMatMulOperator;
1101 matmul->inputs = {node.input(0), node.input(1)};
1102 matmul->outputs = {node.name()};
1103 model->operators.emplace_back(matmul);
1104}

1106void ConvertConcatOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1107 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1108 Model* model) {
1109 Operator* op = nullptr;
1110 if (node.op() == "Concat") {
1111 op = new TensorFlowConcatOperator;
1112 } else if (node.op() == "ConcatV2") {
1113 op = new TensorFlowConcatV2Operator;
1114 } else {
1115 LOG(FATAL) << "Expected Concat or ConcatV2";
1116 }
1117 const int num_inputs = GetInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags);
1118 QCHECK_GE(num_inputs, 2)
1119 << node.op()
1120 << " node expects at least 2 inputs other than control dependencies: "
1121 << node.DebugString();
1122 CHECK_EQ(num_inputs, 1 + GetIntAttr(node, "N"));
1123 for (int i = 0; i < num_inputs; ++i) {
1124 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(i));
1125 }
1126 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1127 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1128}

1169void ConvertLessEqualOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1170 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1171 Model* model) {
1172 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "LessEqual");
1173 auto* op = new TensorFlowLessEqualOperator;
1174 const int num_inputs = GetInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags);
1175 for (int i = 0; i < num_inputs; ++i) {
1176 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(i));
1177 }
1178 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1179 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1180}

1262void ConvertUnsupportedOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1263 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1264 Model* model) {
1265 LOG(INFO) << "Converting unsupported operation: " << node.op();
1266 auto* op = new TensorFlowUnsupportedOperator;
1267 const int num_inputs = GetInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags);
1268 for (int i = 0; i < num_inputs; ++i) {
1269 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(i));
1270 }
1271 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1272 op->tensorflow_op = node.op();
1273 node.SerializeToString(&op->tensorflow_node_def);
1274 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1275 if (HasAttr(node, "_output_quantized")) {
1276 op->quantized = GetBoolAttr(node, "_output_quantized");
1277 }
1278 if (HasAttr(node, "_output_types")) {
1279 const auto& output_types = GetListAttr(node, "_output_types");
1280 for (int i = 0; i < output_types.type_size(); ++i) {
1281 op->output_data_types.push_back(ConvertDataType(output_types.type(i)));
1282 }
1283 }
1284}

1307
1308void ConvertPlaceholderOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1309 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1310 Model* model) {
1311 CHECK(node.op() == "Placeholder" || node.op() == "LegacyFedInput");
1312 if (node.op() == "Placeholder") {
1313 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 0);
1314 }
1315 auto& array = model->GetOrCreateArray(node.name());
1316 if (node.attr().count("dtype")) {
1317 array.data_type = ConvertDataType(GetDataTypeAttr(node, "dtype"));
1318 }
1319 if (node.attr().count("shape")) {
1320 const auto& shape = GetShapeAttr(node, "shape");
1321 auto num_dims = shape.dim_size();
1322 bool has_wildcard = false;
1323 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < num_dims; i++) {
1324 if (shape.dim(i).size() == -1) {
1325 has_wildcard = true;
1326 }
1327 }
1328 // TODO(b/62716978): This logic needs to be revisted. During dims
1329 // refactoring it is an interim fix.
1330 if (num_dims > 0 && !has_wildcard) {
1331 auto& dst_array_dims = *array.mutable_shape()->mutable_dims();
1332 dst_array_dims.resize(num_dims);
1333 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < num_dims; i++) {
1334 dst_array_dims[i] = shape.dim(i).size();
1335 }
1336 }
1337 }
1338}

1423
1424void ConvertBatchNormWithGlobalNormalizationOperator(
1425 const NodeDef& node, const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1426 Model* model) {
1427 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "BatchNormWithGlobalNormalization");
1428 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 5);
1429
1430 // TODO(ahentz): to really match tensorflow we need to add variance_epsilon
1431 // to the input, before feeding it into TensorFlowRsqrtOperator.
1432 // CHECK_EQ(GetFloatAttr(node, "variance_epsilon"), 0.001f);
1433
1434 string multiplier = node.name() + "_mul";
1435 if (GetBoolAttr(node, "scale_after_normalization")) {
1436 // Create graph:
1437 // v -> RSQRT ->
1438 // MUL -> multiplier
1439 // gamma ----->
1440 string rsqrt = node.name() + "_rsqrt";
1441
1442 auto* rsqrt_op = new TensorFlowRsqrtOperator;
1443 rsqrt_op->inputs.push_back(node.input(2));
1444 rsqrt_op->outputs.push_back(rsqrt);
1445 model->operators.emplace_back(rsqrt_op);
1446
1447 auto* mul_op = new MulOperator;
1448 mul_op->inputs.push_back(rsqrt);
1449 mul_op->inputs.push_back(node.input(4));
1450 mul_op->outputs.push_back(multiplier);
1451 model->operators.emplace_back(mul_op);
1452 } else {
1453 // Create graph:
1454 // v -> RSQRT -> multiplier
1455 auto* rsqrt_op = new TensorFlowRsqrtOperator;
1456 rsqrt_op->inputs.push_back(node.input(2));
1457 rsqrt_op->outputs.push_back(multiplier);
1458 model->operators.emplace_back(rsqrt_op);
1459 }
1460
1461 auto* op = new BatchNormalizationOperator;
1462 op->global_normalization = true;
1463
1464 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1465 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(1));
1466 op->inputs.push_back(multiplier);
1467 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(3));
1468 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1469
1470 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1471}
1472
1473void ConvertFusedBatchNormOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1474 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1475 Model* model) {
1476 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "FusedBatchNorm");
1477 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 5);
1478
1479 // Declare shortcuts for the inputs.
1480 const string& gamma_input = node.input(1);
1481 const string& beta_input = node.input(2);
1482 const string& moving_mean_input = node.input(3);
1483 const string& moving_variance_input = node.input(4);
1484
1485 // Create an array holding the epsilon value (typically, 0.001).
1486 const string epsilon_array_name = CreateConstArray<ArrayDataType::kFloat>(
1487 model, node.name() + "_epsilon_array", {GetFloatAttr(node, "epsilon")});
1488
1489 // Add epsilon to the moving variance.
1490 const string epsilon_add_op_name = node.name() + "_epsilon";
1491 auto* epsilon_add_op = new AddOperator;
1492 epsilon_add_op->inputs.push_back(moving_variance_input);
1493 epsilon_add_op->inputs.push_back(epsilon_array_name);
1494 epsilon_add_op->outputs.push_back(epsilon_add_op_name);
1495 model->operators.emplace_back(epsilon_add_op);
1496
1497 // Take the inverse square root of the (variance + epsilon).
1498 const string rsqrt_op_name = node.name() + "_rsqrt";
1499 auto* rsqrt_op = new TensorFlowRsqrtOperator;
1500 rsqrt_op->inputs.push_back(epsilon_add_op_name);
1501 rsqrt_op->outputs.push_back(rsqrt_op_name);
1502 model->operators.emplace_back(rsqrt_op);
1503
1504 // Multiply the result by gamma.
1505 const string multiplier = node.name() + "_mul";
1506 auto* mul_op = new MulOperator;
1507 mul_op->inputs.push_back(rsqrt_op_name);
1508 mul_op->inputs.push_back(gamma_input);
1509 mul_op->outputs.push_back(multiplier);
1510 model->operators.emplace_back(mul_op);
1511
1512 // Now we have all required inputs for the BatchNormalizationOperator.
1513 auto* op = new BatchNormalizationOperator;
1514 op->global_normalization = true;
1515
1516 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1517 op->inputs.push_back(moving_mean_input);
1518 op->inputs.push_back(multiplier);
1519 op->inputs.push_back(beta_input);
1520 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1521
1522 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1523}

1583void ConvertSvdfOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1584 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1585 Model* model) {
1586 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "Svdf");
1587 const int input_size = GetInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags);
1588 QCHECK(input_size == 3 || input_size == 4)
1589 << "Svdf node expects 3 or 4 inputs other than control dependencies: "
1590 << node.DebugString();
1591 bool has_bias = (input_size == 4);
1592 auto* op = new SvdfOperator;
1593 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1594 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(1));
1595 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(2));
1596 if (has_bias) {
1597 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(3));
1598 }
1599 op->outputs.push_back(node.name() + "_state");
1600 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1601 if (node.attr().at("ActivationFunction").s() == "Relu") {
1602 op->fused_activation_function = FusedActivationFunctionType::kRelu;
1603 } else {
1604 op->fused_activation_function = FusedActivationFunctionType::kNone;
1605 }
1606 op->rank = node.attr().at("Rank").i();
1607 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1608}
1609
1610// This is just bare bones support to get the shapes to propagate.
1611void ConvertTransposeConvOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1612 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1613 Model* model) {
1614 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "Conv2DBackpropInput");
1615 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 3);
1616 auto* op = new TransposeConvOperator;
1617 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1618 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(1));
1619 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(2));
1620 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1621 const auto& strides = GetListAttr(node, "strides");
1622 op->stride_height = strides.i(1);
1623 op->stride_width = strides.i(2);
1624 CHECK_EQ(strides.i_size(), 4)
1625 << "Can only import TransposeConv ops with 4D strides. TensorFlow op \""
1626 << node.name() << "\" has " << strides.i_size() << "D strides.";
1627 CHECK((strides.i(0) == 1) && (strides.i(3) == 1))
1628 << "Can only import TransposeConv ops with striding along the height "
1629 "(1st) or width (2nd) axis. TensorFlow op \""
1630 << node.name() << "\" had strides:[ " << strides.i(0) << ", "
1631 << strides.i(1) << ", " << strides.i(2) << ", " << strides.i(3) << "].";
1632 op->stride_height = strides.i(1);
1633 op->stride_width = strides.i(2);
1634 if (HasAttr(node, "dilations")) {
1635 const auto& dilations = GetListAttr(node, "dilations");
1636 CHECK_EQ(dilations.i_size(), 4)
1637 << "Dilation unsupported in TransposeConv. TensorFlow op \""
1638 << node.name() << "\" had dilations";
1639 CHECK((dilations.i(0) == 1) && (dilations.i(1) == 1) &&
1640 (dilations.i(1) == 1) && (dilations.i(3) == 1))
1641 << "Dilation unsupported in TransposeConv. TensorFlow op \""
1642 << node.name() << "\" had dilations:[ " << dilations.i(0) << ", "
1643 << dilations.i(1) << ", " << dilations.i(2) << ", " << dilations.i(3)
1644 << "].";
1645 }
1646
1647 const string& weights_name = node.input(TransposeConvOperator::WEIGHTS);
1648 const string& transposed_weights_name = weights_name + "_transposed";
1649 // Check if a TransposeOperator was already created for these weights
1650 // (can happen when multiple layers share the same weights).
1651 const Operator* existing_transpose =
1652 GetOpWithOutput(*model, transposed_weights_name);
1653 if (existing_transpose) {
1654 CHECK(existing_transpose->type == OperatorType::kTranspose);
1655 } else {
1656 // Transpose weights from HWIO order to OHWI order, which is more efficient
1657 // for computation
1658 TransposeOperator* transpose = new TransposeOperator;
1659 string perm_array = CreateConstArray<ArrayDataType::kInt32>(
1660 model, node.name() + "_transpose_perm", {3, 0, 1, 2});
1661 transpose->inputs = {weights_name, perm_array};
1662 transpose->outputs = {transposed_weights_name};
1663 model->operators.emplace_back(transpose);
1664 }
1665 op->inputs[1] = transposed_weights_name;
1666
1667 auto const& padding = GetStringAttr(node, "padding");
1668 if (padding == "SAME") {
1669 op->padding.type = PaddingType::kSame;
1670 } else if (padding == "VALID") {
1671 op->padding.type = PaddingType::kValid;
1672 } else {
1673 LOG(FATAL) << "Only SAME and VALID padding supported on "
1674 "Conv2DBackpropInput nodes.";
1675 }
1676 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1677}

1714
1715void ConvertFloorModOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1716 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1717 Model* model) {
1718 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "FloorMod");
1719 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 2);
1720 auto* op = new FloorModOperator;
1721 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1722 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(1));
1723 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1724 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1725}

1727void ConvertRangeOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1728 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1729 Model* model) {
1730 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "Range");
1731 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 3);
1732 auto* op = new RangeOperator;
1733 if (HasAttr(node, "Tidx")) {
1734 const auto dtype = toco::GetDataTypeAttr(node, "Tidx");
1735 CHECK(dtype == DT_UINT8 || dtype == DT_INT32 || dtype == DT_INT64 ||
1736 dtype == DT_FLOAT);
1737 op->dtype = ConvertDataType(dtype);
1738 }
1739 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1740 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(1));
1741 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(2));
1742 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1743 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1744}

1747 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1748 Model* model) {
1749 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "Rank");
1750 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 1);
1751 auto* op = new RankOperator;
1752 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1753 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1754 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1755}

1757void ConvertStackOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1758 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1759 Model* model) {
1760 CHECK((node.op() == "Stack") || (node.op() == "Pack"));
1761 auto* op = new StackOperator;
1762 const int num_inputs = GetInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags);
1763 QCHECK_GE(num_inputs, 1)
1764 << node.op()
1765 << " node expects at least 1 input other than control dependencies: "
1766 << node.DebugString();
1767 CHECK_EQ(num_inputs, GetIntAttr(node, "N"));
1768 for (int i = 0; i < num_inputs; ++i) {
1769 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(i));
1770 }
1771 // Both "Stack" and "Pack" have the "axis" attribute.
1772 op->axis = GetIntAttr(node, "axis");
1773 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1774 model->operators.emplace_back(op);
1775}

1781 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 2);

1783 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1784 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(1));
1785 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
1786 model->operators.emplace_back(op);

1788
1789// Some TensorFlow ops only occur in graph cycles, representing
1790// control flow. We do not currently support control flow, so we wouldn't
1791// be able to fully support such graphs, including performing inference,
1792// anyway. However, rather than erroring out early on graphs being cyclic,
1793// it helps to at least support these just enough to allow getting a
1794// graph visualization. This is not trivial, as we require graphs to be
1795// acyclic aside from RNN back-edges. The solution is to special-case
1796// such ops as RNN back-edges, which is technically incorrect (does not
1797// allow representing the op's semantics) but good enough to get a
1798// graph visualization.
1799void ConvertOperatorSpecialCasedAsRNNBackEdge(
1800 const NodeDef& node, const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1801 Model* model) {
1802 // At the moment, the only type of operator special-cased in this way is
1803 // NextIteration, occurring only in control-flow cycles.
1804 CHECK_EQ(node.op(), "NextIteration");
1805 CHECK_EQ(node.input_size(), 1);
1806 auto* rnn_state = model->flags.add_rnn_states();
1807 // This RNN state is not explicitly created by the user, so it's
1808 // OK for some later graph transformation to discard it.
1809 rnn_state->set_discardable(true);
1810 rnn_state->set_state_array(node.name());
1811 rnn_state->set_back_edge_source_array(node.input(0));
1812}
1813
1814void StripCaretFromArrayNames(Model* model) {
1815 for (auto& op : model->operators) {
1816 for (auto& input : op->inputs) {
1817 input = string(absl::StripPrefix(input, "^"));
1818 }
1819 for (auto& output : op->outputs) {
1820 output = string(absl::StripPrefix(output, "^"));
1821 }
1822 }
1823 for (auto& array : model->GetArrayMap()) {
1824 if (absl::StartsWith(array.first, "^")) {
1825 LOG(FATAL) << "What?";
1826 }
1827 }
1828}
1829
1830void StripZeroOutputIndexFromInputs(NodeDef* node) {
1831 for (auto& input : *node->mutable_input()) {
1832 input = string(absl::StripSuffix(input, ":0"));
1833 }
1834}
1835
1836// In TensorFlow GraphDef, when a node has multiple outputs, they are named
1837// name:0, name:1, ...
1838// where 'name' is the node's name(). Just 'name' is an equivalent shorthand
1839// form for name:0.
1840// A TensorFlow GraphDef does not explicitly list all the outputs of each node
1841// (unlike inputs), it being implied by the node's name and operator type
1842// (the latter implies the number of outputs).
1843// This makes it non-trivial for us to reconstruct the list of all arrays
1844// present in the graph and, for each operator, the list of its outputs.
1845// We do that by taking advantage of the fact that
1846// at least each node lists explicitly its inputs, so after we've loaded
1847// all nodes, we can use that information.
1848void AddExtraOutputs(Model* model) {
1849 // Construct the list of all arrays consumed by anything in the graph.
1850 std::vector<string> consumed_arrays;
1851 // Add arrays consumed by an op.
1852 for (const auto& consumer_op : model->operators) {
1853 for (const string& input : consumer_op->inputs) {
1854 consumed_arrays.push_back(input);
1855 }
1856 }
1857 // Add global outputs of the model.
1858 for (const string& output_array : model->flags.output_arrays()) {
1859 consumed_arrays.push_back(output_array);
1860 }
1861 // Add arrays consumed by a RNN back-edge.
1862 for (const auto& rnn_state : model->flags.rnn_states()) {
1863 consumed_arrays.push_back(rnn_state.back_edge_source_array());
1864 }
1865 // Now add operator outputs so that all arrays that are consumed,
1866 // are produced.
1867 for (const string& consumed_array : consumed_arrays) {
1868 // Split the consumed array name into the form name:output_index.
1869 const std::vector<string>& split = absl::StrSplit(consumed_array, ':');
1870 // If not of the form name:output_index, then this is not an additional
1871 // output of a node with multiple outputs, so nothing to do here.
1872 if (split.size() != 2) {
1873 continue;
1874 }
1875 int output_index = 0;
1876 if (!absl::SimpleAtoi(split[1], &output_index)) {
1877 continue;
1878 }
1879 // Each op is initially recorded as producing at least the array that
1880 // has its name. We use that to identify the producer node.
1881 auto* producer_op = GetOpWithOutput(*model, split[0]);
1882 if (!producer_op) {
1883 continue;
1884 }
1885 // Add extra outputs to that producer node, all the way to the
1886 // output_index.
1887 while (producer_op->outputs.size() <= output_index) {
1888 using toco::port::StringF;
1889 producer_op->outputs.push_back(
1890 StringF("%s:%d", split[0], producer_op->outputs.size()));
1891 }
1892 }
1893}
1894
1895bool InlineAllFunctions(GraphDef* graphdef) {
1896 if (graphdef->library().function().empty()) {
1897 VLOG(kLogLevelModelUnchanged) << "No functions to inline.";
1898 return false;
1899 }
1900
1901 // Override "_noinline" attribute on all functions
1902 GraphDef graphdef_copy(*graphdef);
1903 for (auto& function :
1904 (*graphdef_copy.mutable_library()->mutable_function())) {
1905 auto* attributes = function.mutable_attr();
1906 if (attributes->count(tensorflow::kNoInlineAttr) != 0) {
1907 (*attributes)[tensorflow::kNoInlineAttr].set_b(false);
1908 }
1909 }
1910
1911 // Construct minimum resources needed to use ExpandInlineFunctions().
1912 tensorflow::SessionOptions options;
1913 auto* device_count = options.config.mutable_device_count();
1914 device_count->insert({"CPU", 1});
1915 std::vector<tensorflow::Device*> devices;
1916 TF_CHECK_OK(tensorflow::DeviceFactory::AddDevices(
1917 options, "/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0", &devices));
1918
1919 tensorflow::FunctionLibraryDefinition fld(tensorflow::OpRegistry::Global(),
1920 graphdef_copy.library());
1921 tensorflow::DeviceMgr device_mgr(devices);
1922 tensorflow::OptimizerOptions o_opts;
1923 tensorflow::ProcessFunctionLibraryRuntime pflr(
1924 &device_mgr, tensorflow::Env::Default(), TF_GRAPH_DEF_VERSION, &fld,
1925 o_opts, nullptr);
1926 tensorflow::FunctionLibraryRuntime* flr;
1927 flr = pflr.GetFLR("/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/cpu:0");
1928
1929 tensorflow::Graph graph(fld);
1930 tensorflow::ImportGraphDefOptions gc_opts;
1931 gc_opts.validate_shape = false;
1932 const auto& tf_convert_status = tensorflow::ImportGraphDef(
1933 gc_opts, graphdef_copy, &graph, nullptr, nullptr);
1934 if (!tf_convert_status.ok()) {
1935 LOG(ERROR) << "tensorflow::ImportGraphDef failed with status: "
1936 << tf_convert_status.ToString();
1937 return false;
1938 }
1939
1940 // Iterate over the graph until there are no more nodes to be inlined.
1941 bool graph_modified = false;
1942 while (tensorflow::ExpandInlineFunctions(flr, &graph)) {
1943 graph_modified = true;
1944 }
1945
1946 // Output inlined graph
1947 if (graph_modified) {
1948 LOG(INFO) << "Found and inlined TensorFlow functions.";
1949 graph.ToGraphDef(graphdef);
1950 }
1951 return graph_modified;
1952}

1954void ConvertTopKV2Operator(const NodeDef& node,
1955 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1956 Model* model) {
1957 CHECK((node.op() == "TopK") || (node.op() == "TopKV2"));
1958 auto op = absl::make_unique<TopKV2Operator>();
1959 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1960 // K can be encoded as attr (TopK) convert it to a const.
1961 if (HasAttr(node, "k")) {
1962 string k_array = CreateConstArray<ArrayDataType::kInt32>(
1963 model, node.name() + "k", {static_cast<int32>(GetIntAttr(node, "k"))});
1964 op->inputs.push_back(k_array);
1965 } else {
1966 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 2);
1967 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(1));
1968 }
1969 // The op has two outputs.
1970 op->outputs.push_back(node.name() + ":0");
1971 op->outputs.push_back(node.name() + ":1");
1972 model->operators.emplace_back(op.release());
1973}
1974
1975void ConvertDynamicPartitionOperator(
1976 const NodeDef& node, const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1977 Model* model) {
1978 auto op = absl::make_unique<DynamicPartitionOperator>();
1979 CHECK(HasAttr(node, "num_partitions"));
1980 op->num_partitions = GetIntAttr(node, "num_partitions");
1981 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, 2);
1982 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(0));
1983 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(1));
1984 CHECK_GT(op->num_partitions, 1);
1985 op->outputs.push_back(node.name()); // Implicit :0.
1986 for (int i = 1; i < op->num_partitions; ++i) {
1987 op->outputs.push_back(node.name() + ":" + std::to_string(i));
1988 }
1989 model->operators.emplace_back(op.release());
1990}
1991
1992void ConvertDynamicStitchOperator(const NodeDef& node,
1993 const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
1994 Model* model) {
1995 // The parallel and non-parallel variants are the same besides whether they
1996 // have a parallel loop; there are no behavioral differences.
1997 CHECK(node.op() == "DynamicStitch" || node.op() == "ParallelDynamicStitch");
1998 auto op = absl::make_unique<DynamicStitchOperator>();
1999 CHECK(HasAttr(node, "N"));
2000 op->num_partitions = GetIntAttr(node, "N");
2001 // Expect all ID partitions + all value partitions.
2002 CheckInputsCount(node, tf_import_flags, op->num_partitions * 2);
2003 for (int i = 0; i < op->num_partitions * 2; ++i) {
2004 op->inputs.push_back(node.input(i));
2005 }
2006 op->outputs.push_back(node.name());
2007 model->operators.emplace_back(op.release());
2008}

2012std::unique_ptr<Model> ImportTensorFlowGraphDef(
2013 const ModelFlags& model_flags, const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
2014 const GraphDef& tf_graph) {
2015 LogDumpGraphDef(kLogLevelModelChanged, "AT IMPORT", tf_graph);
2016
2017 GraphDef inlined_graph(tf_graph);
2018 if (InlineAllFunctions(&inlined_graph)) {
2019 LogDumpGraphDef(kLogLevelModelChanged, "AFTER INLINING", inlined_graph);
2020 }
2021
2022 // Check input and output specification.
2023 for (const auto& specified_input_array : model_flags.input_arrays()) {
2024 CHECK(!absl::EndsWith(specified_input_array.name(), ":0"))
2025 << "Unsupported explicit zero output index: "
2026 << specified_input_array.name();
2027 }
2028 for (const string& specified_output_array : model_flags.output_arrays()) {
2029 CHECK(!absl::EndsWith(specified_output_array, ":0"))
2030 << "Unsupported explicit zero output index: " << specified_output_array;
2031 }

2044 ConvertDepthwiseConvOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2045 } else if (node.op() == "DepthToSpace") {
2046 ConvertDepthToSpaceOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2047 } else if (node.op() == "SpaceToDepth") {
2048 ConvertSpaceToDepthOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2049 } else if (node.op() == "BiasAdd") {
2050 ConvertBiasAddOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2051 } else if (node.op() == "Relu") {
2052 ConvertReluOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2053 } else if (node.op() == "Relu6") {
2054 ConvertRelu6Operator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2055 } else if (node.op() == "Sigmoid") {
2056 ConvertLogisticOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2057 } else if (node.op() == "Tanh") {
2058 ConvertTanhOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2059 } else if (node.op() == "MaxPool") {
2060 ConvertMaxPoolOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2061 } else if (node.op() == "AvgPool") {
2062 ConvertAvgPoolOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2063 } else if (node.op() == "Reshape") {
2064 ConvertReshapeOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2065 } else if (node.op() == "BatchMatMul") {
2066 ConvertBatchMatMulOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2067 } else if (node.op() == "MatMul") {
2068 ConvertMatMulOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2069 } else if (node.op() == "Div" || node.op() == "RealDiv") {
2070 ConvertDivOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2071 } else if (node.op() == "Identity" || node.op() == "CheckNumerics" ||
2072 node.op() == "StopGradient") {
2073 ConvertIdentityOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2074 } else if (node.op() == "FakeQuantWithMinMaxVars") {
2075 ConvertFakeQuantWithMinMaxVars(node, tf_import_flags, model);

2077 ConvertFakeQuantWithMinMaxArgs(node, tf_import_flags, model);

2079 ConvertNegOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);

2081 ConvertRsqrtOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);

2083 ConvertSqueezeOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2084 } else if (node.op() == "Sqrt") {
2085 ConvertSqrtOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);

2087 ConvertSquareOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);

2159 ConvertResizeBilinearOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);

2174 ConvertOperatorSpecialCasedAsRNNBackEdge(node, tf_import_flags, model);

2187 } else if (node.op() == "Stack" || node.op() == "Pack") {
2188 ConvertStackOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2189 } else if (node.op() == "Transpose") {
2190 ConvertTransposeOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2191 } else if (node.op() == "ArgMax") {
2192 ConvertArgMaxOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2193 } else if (node.op() == "Exp") {
2194 ConvertExpOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2195 } else if (node.op() == "TopK" || node.op() == "TopKV2") {
2196 ConvertTopKV2Operator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2197 } else if (node.op() == "DynamicPartition") {
2198 ConvertDynamicPartitionOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2199 } else if (node.op() == "DynamicStitch" ||
2200 node.op() == "ParallelDynamicStitch") {
2201 ConvertDynamicStitchOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2202 } else if (node.op() == "RandomUniform") {
2203 ConvertRandomUniform(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2204 } else {
2205 ConvertUnsupportedOperator(node, tf_import_flags, model);
2206 }
2207 }
2208
2209 ResolveModelFlags(model_flags, model);
2210
2211 StripCaretFromArrayNames(model);
2212 AddExtraOutputs(model);
2213 FixNoMissingArray(model);
2214 FixNoOrphanedArray(model);
2215 FixOperatorOrdering(model);
2216 CheckInvariants(*model);
2217
2218 // if rnn state arrays are constant, make them transient
2219 for (const auto& rnn_state : model->flags.rnn_states()) {
2220 model->GetArray(rnn_state.state_array()).buffer = nullptr;
2221 }
2222
2223 return std::unique_ptr<Model>(model);
2224}
2225
2226std::unique_ptr<Model> ImportTensorFlowGraphDef(
2227 const ModelFlags& model_flags, const TensorFlowImportFlags& tf_import_flags,
2228 const string& input_file_contents) {
2229 std::unique_ptr<GraphDef> tf_graph(new GraphDef);
2230 CHECK(ParseFromStringEitherTextOrBinary(input_file_contents, tf_graph.get()));
2231
2232 std::unique_ptr<GraphDef> pruned_graph =
2233 MaybeReplaceCompositeSubgraph(*tf_graph);
2234 if (pruned_graph) {
2235 tf_graph = std::move(pruned_graph);
2236 }
2237 return ImportTensorFlowGraphDef(model_flags, tf_import_flags, *tf_graph);
2238}
